{%- comment -%}
  Ganguram — Driving-distance config (Phase 2.11D).

  Publishes window.GanguramDistanceConfig (outlet origin + enable flag) and loads
  assets/ganguram-distance.js (window.GanguramDistance). REUSES the Phase 2.9B
  Google key via window.GanguramPlaces.loadMaps; it needs the Google **Distance
  Matrix API** enabled on that browser key. Used ONLY for FULL-ADDRESS selections
  (driving distance -> a confirmed distanceKm for the cart rules' distance slabs).

  FAIL-OPEN: no outlet origin set / Distance Matrix unavailable -> no confirmed
  distance; the cart stays on the estimated pincode/zone path. No checkout /
  shipping-charge / ShipZip / SBZ / zipLogic / resolver / settings_data.json change.

  Origin is the outlet "lat,lng" from the theme setting `ganguram_outlet_origin`
  (Theme settings -> "Ganguram - Address search"). Enabled only when it is set.
{%- endcomment -%}
<script>
  window.GanguramDistanceConfig = {
    enabled: {% if settings.ganguram_outlet_origin != blank %}true{% else %}false{% endif %},
    origin: {{ settings.ganguram_outlet_origin | default: '' | json }}
  };
</script>
<script src="{{ 'ganguram-distance.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>
